import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

#   
companies = ["A", "B", "C", "D", "E"]
revenues = [400, 600, 800, 200, 500]

# Donut Chart -  
plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
sizes = revenues
labels = companies
colors = sns.color_palette("Purples", len(labels))

#   
wedges, texts, autotexts = plt.pie(
    sizes,
    labels=labels,
    colors=colors,
    wedgeprops=dict(width=0.4),
    startangle=140,
    autopct='%1.1f%%',
    textprops=dict(color="black")
)

#  
for text in autotexts:
    text.set_size(10)  #  
    text.set_color("black")  #  

plt.title("Revenue Distribution", fontsize=14)
plt.show()

# Import required libraries
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd

# Define financial data
data = {
    "Company": ["A", "B", "C", "D", "E"],
    "Revenue": [400, 600, 800, 200, 500],
    "Profit": [150, 200, 300, 50, 120],
    "Expenses": [250, 400, 500, 150, 380],
    "Debt": [100, 150, 200, 80, 120],
    "Cash Flow": [300, 450, 700, 150, 400]
}
df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# Create a professional financial dashboard
plt.figure(figsize=(18, 16))
plt.suptitle("Financial Analysis of Investment Companies", fontsize=22, color="purple", weight="bold")

# Donut Chart: Revenue Distribution
plt.subplot(3, 2, 1)
sizes = df["Revenue"]
labels = df["Company"]
colors = sns.color_palette("Purples", len(labels))
plt.pie(sizes, labels=labels, colors=colors, wedgeprops=dict(width=0.4), startangle=140, autopct='%1.1f%%')
plt.title("Revenue Distribution", fontsize=16)

# Bar Chart: Profit by Company
plt.subplot(3, 2, 2)
sns.barplot(x="Company", y="Profit", data=df, palette="Purples_r")
plt.title("Profit by Company", fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel("Company", fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel("Profit (in USD)", fontsize=12)

# Line Chart: Revenue vs Expenses
plt.subplot(3, 2, 3)
plt.plot(df["Company"], df["Revenue"], marker='o', label="Revenue", color="#6a0dad")
plt.plot(df["Company"], df["Expenses"], marker='o', label="Expenses", color="#dda0dd")
plt.title("Revenue vs Expenses", fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel("Company", fontsize=12)
plt.ylabel("Amount (in USD)", fontsize=12)
plt.legend()

# Heatmap: Profit and Debt Correlation
plt.subplot(3, 2, 4)
heat_data = df[["Profit", "Debt"]].corr()
sns.heatmap(heat_data, annot=True, cmap="Purples", fmt=".2f", cbar=False)
plt.title("Profit vs Debt Correlation", fontsize=16)

# Boxplot: Cash Flow Analysis
plt.subplot(3, 2, 5)
sns.boxplot(data=df["Cash Flow"], color="purple")
plt.title("Cash Flow Analysis", fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel("Cash Flow (in USD)", fontsize=12)

# Scatterplot: Profit vs Expenses
plt.subplot(3, 2, 6)
sns.scatterplot(x="Profit", y="Expenses", data=df, color="darkviolet")
plt.title("Profit vs Expenses", fontsize=16)
plt.xlabel("Profit (in USD)")
plt.ylabel("Expenses (in USD)")

# Adjust layout for better visibility
plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0, 1, 0.95])
plt.show()
